An iconic gesture by the Karnataka Forest Department, honouring the critically endangered Hump-backed Mahseer (Tor remadevii), which like other freshwater fish in the country, does not feature anywhere in the Indian Wildlife Protection Act (1972). 

#worldwildlifeweek2021

